com.ryanantkowiak.jOptionsHouseAPI
Class OptionsHouseUtilities

java.lang.Object
  com.ryanantkowiak.jOptionsHouseAPI.OptionsHouseUtilities

public class OptionsHouseUtilities
extends java.lang.Object

 This class contains some utility methods that are useful when
 dealing with OptionsHouse symbols and keys. Internally, many of the
 OptionsHouse API JSON messages are required to contain the keys for
 stocks and ETFs in a similar format how options contracts are formatted.
 
 For example, option contracts look like: "IBM:20110716:1600000:C" and
 contain 4 pieces of data, separated by a colon ":" character. The
 four pieces of data in order are:
 1) Underlying stock symbol [ex: "IBM"]
 2) Expiration date (YYYYMMDD) [ex: "20110716"]
 3) Strike Price in hundredths of a cent [ex: "1600000"] for $160.00
 4) "C" or "P" for a Call option or Put Option [ex: "C"]
 
 For stocks, the OptionsHouse API internally refers to the security
 as follows:  "IBM:::S"
 
 Where the first part of it is the stock symbol,
 followed by three colons, and then finally a capital letter "S" (for "Stock")

Author:
Ryan Antkowiak

public static boolean DEBUG_MSG_TRACING
Boolean flag to enable debug message tracing output. Warning: This will cause all JSON message data to be printed in clear-text INCLUDING login and password credentials! Only enable this in a secure environment!

normalizeKey

public static java.lang.String normalizeKey(java.lang.String key)
Normalize a key used by OptionsHouse API to specify a particular security. This can be a stock or an option, and must contain colon-separated fields. It will remove all characters except alphanumeric and colons. Also convert it to all upper-case characters.

Parameters:
key - the key of either a stock or option security to be normalized
Returns:
the normalized value of the key
